        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 1:10AM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 110 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Chebanse, or near Kankakee, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bradley, Kankakee, Sammons Point, Sun River Terrace, Bourbonnais,
Momence, Aroma Park, Irwin, and Chebanse.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
